The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                               BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, March 8: Police today busted a chit-fund racket that had collected almost Rs 42 lakh from over 1,000 depositors between 2001 and 2004. Four persons have been arrested. A Nainatal-based company, Crystal Capital Corporation, was behind the racket, the police said.        
	Calcutta: A three-and-a-half-year-old girl died on Friday night, a day after eating at a shradh ceremony in a South 24-Parganas village. Her three siblings had also fallen ill. One of them is in hospital.        
	Calcutta: Suchitra Sen has not yet recovered from her knee pain and is unable to get out of bed but her breathing problem has almost subsided, sources said. She is on normal diet.                                                                                                                                                                       
